				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{AC}\ \left(\%\right)=\left({\mathrm{A}}_{\mathrm{b}}-{\mathrm{A}}_{\mathrm{s}}/{\mathrm{A}}_{\mathrm{b}}\right)\times 100 $$\end{document}AC%=Ab−As/Ab×100Where, AC = antioxidant capacity, Ab = absorbance of the blank sample [10 and 150 μL methanol for DPPH and ABTS, respectively as a substitute of leaf extract], and As = absorbance of the test compound. The results were calculated as μg TEAC g− 1 DW.
